# TypeScript Rules

## Strict Mode

- `strict: true` always.
- No `any` — use `unknown` + narrowing, or proper types.
- No `@ts-ignore` without a comment explaining why.

## Types Organization

```
src/types/
  database/   # Supabase generated types
  domain/     # Plan, Video, Subscription, etc.
  api/        # Request/response shapes
```

## Naming

| Kind | Style | Example |
|------|-------|---------|
| DB columns | snake_case | `current_period_end` |
| TS properties | camelCase | `currentPeriodEnd` |
| Components | PascalCase | `PricingCard` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE | `PLAN_SLUGS` |
| Enums/unions | PascalCase | `SubscriptionStatus` |

## Service Functions

Always explicit return types:

```typescript
export async function canAccessVideo(
  userId: string,
  videoId: string
): Promise<boolean> {
  // ...
}
```

## API Result Type

```typescript
type ActionResult<T> =
  | { success: true; data: T }
  | { success: false; error: { code: string; message: string } }
```

## Provider Types

Isolate Stripe/Mux/Supabase-specific types in `lib/` — don't leak into components.

## Database Types

- Regenerate from Supabase after migrations.
- Map DB rows to domain types in services when shapes differ.

## Validation

- Zod schemas in `features/*/schemas/` or `lib/validation/`.
- Infer types: `type LoginInput = z.infer<typeof loginSchema>`.

## Avoid

```typescript
// ❌
const data: any = await response.json()

// ✅
const parsed = checkoutSchema.safeParse(body)
if (!parsed.success) return validationError(parsed.error)
```
